{"lemma":"ظاهِرَةٌ","slug":"ظاهِرَةٌ","root":"ظ.ه.ر","root_slug":"ظ-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظاهِرَة","root":"ظهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27713","n27734"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"phenomenon"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ظ ه ر (ẓ h r). \"to appear\"."},"ipa":["/ðˤaː.hi.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27713","headword_ar":"ظاهرهُ","root":"Zhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muZaAharapN","text_ar":"مُظَاهَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assisted, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zahara","text_ar":"ظَهَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Th, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhr Ealayohi","text_ar":"ظاهر عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assisted, against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhr bihi","text_ar":"ظاهر بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 10. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhr bayonahumaA","text_ar":"ظاهر بَيْنَهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) i. e. (TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona vawobayoni","text_ar":"بَيْنَ ثَوْبَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroEayoni","text_ar":"دِرْعَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEolayoni","text_ar":"نَعْلَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAraqa bayonahumaA","text_ar":"طَارَقَ بَيْنَهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbaqa","text_ar":"طَابَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K, TA,) i. e. (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put them on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attired himself with them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two coats of mail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sandals"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or rather, when relating to two soles,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sewed them together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outside, the other:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA:) app. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taZaAhurN","text_ar":"تَظَاهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of “ mutual aiding or assisting. ” (IAth.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhr bidiroEayoni","text_ar":"ظاهر بِدِرْعَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"requires consideration; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in it should be regarded as meant to denote conjunction; not as a part of the necessary complement of the verb. (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhr Ald~iroEa","text_ar":"ظاهر الدِّرْعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to signify"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^ama baEoDahaA EalaY baEoDK","text_ar":"لَاَمَ بَعْضَهَا عَلَى بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He folded over and fastened one part of the coat of mail upon another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhr Ealayohi","text_ar":"ظاهر عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilaAlFA","text_ar":"جِلَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"housings"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coverings"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one over another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hn*","text_ar":"حنذ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhr mini A@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"ظاهر مِنِ ا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZihaArN","text_ar":"ظِهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muZaAharapN","text_ar":"مُظَاهَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohaA","text_ar":"مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tZAhr","text_ar":"تظاهر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, O, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZ~aAhara","text_ar":"اِظَّاهَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnhA","text_ar":"منها"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tZh~r","text_ar":"تظهّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZ~ah~ara","text_ar":"اِظَّهَّرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnhA","text_ar":"منها"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zh~r","text_ar":"ظهّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taZohiyrN","text_ar":"تَظْهِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) signify the same; (O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said to his wife"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoti EalaY~a kaZahori A^um~iY","text_ar":"اَنْتِ عَلَىَّ كَظَهْرِ اُمِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art to me like the back of my mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) [as though he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwbuki","text_ar":"رُكُوبُكِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAmN EalaY~a","text_ar":"حَرَامٌ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwbuki liln~ikaAHi HaraAmN EalaY~a","text_ar":"رُكُوبُكِ لِلنِّكَاحِ حَرَامٌ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karukuwbi A^um~iY liln~ikaAHi","text_ar":"كَرُكُوبِ اُمِّى لِلنِّكَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the back being specified in preference to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxi*","text_ar":"فَخِذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroj","text_ar":"فَرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the woman is likened to a beast that is ridden, and the act of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikaAH","text_ar":"نِكَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"to that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwb","text_ar":"رُكُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":": the phrase being a form of divorce used by the Arabs in the Time of Ignorance. (Msb, * TA.) In the Kur lviii. 2 [and 4], some read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZ~ah~aruwna","text_ar":"يَظَّهَّرُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; some ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZ~aAharuwna","text_ar":"يَظَّاهَرُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and 'Ásim read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuZaAhiruwna","text_ar":"يُظَاهِرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.) The verb is made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min","text_ar":"مِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the man who uttered this sentence estranged himself from his wife. (IAth.)"}],"source_refs":["A","S","O","Msb","K","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n27734","headword_ar":"ظَاهِرَةٌ","root":"Zhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"as a subst.; and its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZawaAhiru","text_ar":"ظَوَاهِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahorN","text_ar":"ظَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places, in the third quarter of the paragraph. [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurayo$u AlZ~awaAhiri","text_ar":"قُرَيْشُ الظَّوَاهِرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those, of Kureysh, that dwell in the exterior of Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the mountains thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the higher parts of Mekkeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) those who dwell in the lower parts are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurayo$u AlbiTaAHi","text_ar":"قُرَيْشُ البِطَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, * TA;) and these are the more honourable, (O, TA, *) because they are neighbours of the House of God. (O.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZihaArapN","text_ar":"ظِهَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahiyrN","text_ar":"ظَهِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels, (S, O, K, TA,) and of sheep or goats, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the water every day, at noon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA.) One says, of camels, [and of sheep or goats,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taridu AlZ~aAhirapa","text_ar":"تَرِدُ الظَّاهِرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They come to the water every day, at noon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and Sh says that they return from the water at the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSor","text_ar":"عَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariba Alfarasu ZaAhirapF","text_ar":"شَرِبَ الفَرَسُ ظَاهِرَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horse drank every day, at noon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirapu Algib~i","text_ar":"ظَاهِرَةُ الغِبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The coming to the water at noon on alternate days"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is for sheep or goats; scarcely ever, or never, for camels; and is a little shorter [in the interval] than what is called [simply]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algib~u","text_ar":"الغِبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","TA","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}